From 6e9a28d52017e98defa9e7480b189c18495e1a6a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: John Crispin <john@phrozen.org>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 08:10:20 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] mediatek: filogic: silence MEDIATEK_2P5GE_PHY config prompt

patches-base/0010 dropped CONFIG_MEDIATEK_2P5GE_PHY=y from
filogic/config-6.12 so the driver can build as a module via the
kmod-mt798x-2p5g-phy package (KConfig=m) imported from
feeds/mtk-app. Without an explicit setting, make oldconfig
prompts for the symbol as NEW on every build.

Add an explicit '# CONFIG_MEDIATEK_2P5GE_PHY is not set' so the
symbol stays unset by default; the kmod package still promotes
it to =m when selected.

Signed-off-by: John Crispin <john@phrozen.org>
---
 target/linux/mediatek/filogic/config-6.12 | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/target/linux/mediatek/filogic/config-6.12 b/target/linux/mediatek/filogic/config-6.12
index a2277e45ef..36407a31e0 100644
--- a/target/linux/mediatek/filogic/config-6.12
+++ b/target/linux/mediatek/filogic/config-6.12
@@ -257,6 +257,7 @@ CONFIG_MDIO_AN8855=y
 CONFIG_MDIO_BUS=y
 CONFIG_MDIO_DEVICE=y
 CONFIG_MDIO_DEVRES=y
+# CONFIG_MEDIATEK_2P5GE_PHY is not set
 CONFIG_MEDIATEK_GE_PHY=y
 CONFIG_MEDIATEK_GE_SOC_PHY=y
 CONFIG_MEDIATEK_WATCHDOG=y
-- 
2.34.1

